omass, and exposure time were the most important variables describing differences in assemblage composition. That the Wadden Sea forms a heterogeneous landscape where assemblage composition varies across multiple gradients has repercussions for management and monitoring.},
author = {Compton, Tanya J and Holthuijsen, Sander and Koolhaas, Anita and Dekinga, Anne and ten Horn, Job and Smith, Jeremy and Galama, Ysbrand and Brugge, Maarten and van der Wal, Daphne and van der Meer, Jaap and van der Veer, Henk W and Piersma, Theunis},
